Anonymous Wed 21 Dec 2022 13:57:05 No.53172302 Report

>>53163921
As someone that has written novels twice the length of your draft, tale a week off. Come back to it, but only to deal with the outline. Usually, when I get that off feeling, it's because I have a missing or incomplete scene. My brain knows it, and the parts after feel less and less complete.
It could also be one of a number of other things. You're thematicaly missing a needed character, have two that are too close in purpose, or have scenes that are too fast or slow for the surrounding pacing/plot.

Unless you want to write the simplest stuff, novel-length material is served well by cycles of review and drafts.
